<br>
From levels 1 to 52 about, my mage and druid made an excellent two boxing combo.  Healing the pet was never really something that was really required at those levels so the druid was able to take an offensive roll and I basically had two nukers.  <br>
<br>
There are very few mobs in that in those levels the two combos will have problems with. Mobs that are highly spell resistant, then the fight is won by keeping the pet alive.  A mob that would tear you up in melee, then it becomes a matter of the druid making the mob mad enough to chase while the pet beats from behind. <br>
<br>
Those were very fun times and very easy to fight anywhere with those two, but that changed a bit later on in level.<br>
<br>
After 52, more around 55 I would guess, healing my pet seemed to be more of an issue.  I then switched from mage/druid combo to mage/cleric combo.  <br>
<br>
The mage/cleric combo is outstanding when two-boxing in all non-pop zone.  There are very few mobs you cant handle with this combo.  It also comes in very handy outside of soloing since your guild will love to have you play your cleric in raids and usually choose your cleric over your mage, but if you can two box them during a raid, then you will have a lot more fun during that raid.   I am not saying playing a cleric on a raid is boring, just not as much fun as playing a mage.<br>
<br>
I have barely tried two boxing in PoP so I might be off with this one but with the DPS of the mobs and their hit points, I do not think the mage/cleric combo would work as well.  <br>
<br>
I would love to try a mage/necro combo one day.  The necro fear with two pets beating on a retreating mob would be a killer combination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bloodlilly>Bloodlilly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/03 2:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8754.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2 - Boxing ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Don't PL a chanter, clear a spot on your mage account, to put a lowby melee type. Equip him with good gear, group him with the chanter, to get the chanter the xp. Casters are just too danged hard to PL by themselves, you need something that can take a beating or a chanter to PL them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
