</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scrubfire>scrubfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/03 3:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8754.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2 - Boxing ?</span><hr size=1> Pre level 61, two boxing with cleric/mage in PoP was not possible.  You had to pretty much chain cast CH to keep you pet alive.  I could manage rats in PoD with enchanter/mage using slow and melee debuffs and chaining Greater Vocerate Earth.<br>
<br>
I just dinged 61 a couple of nights ago and tried my hand at pet tanking with cleric buffs (level 52) and comlete heal.  It worked quite well in PoN against Blood Ravens and Gnarled Treants.  I haven't tried it with slow, but I can imagine that it as well will be feasable.  Having the level 60 heal would help tremedously to patch up the pet from the damage it will take before slow lands.<br>
<br>
I've also two boxed a bard/mage which has also been suprisingly effective.  Some of the tactics I've used are using the earth pet as a root (and a very damaging one at that) and bard twisting slow and 3 dots (~200 damage per tick in DoTs).  I've also used bard kiting with backstabbing pet, which worked quite effectively in PoP.  Bards also bring a lot of great utility spells to the table including the fast travel, mana and hp regeneration and tracking.  The biggest downside is that bard songs do not affect pets.<br>
<br>
One other thing I would like to mention about grouping other classes with mages, is the mage ability to debuff mobs resists.  This has had an incredible impact with my duo's where they are casting on the mob.  My bard is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>rarely</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> resisted after malosini, and my enchanter has landed slow (at level 46) on mobs 12 levels higher after malosini/tash combo.  Of course that's a good way to splat your enchanter... thank god for the cleric with all the AA's chain casting heals while the tank got aggro back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p>--------------------------<br>
